The paper deals with instance search and re-identification, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM). The use of category-specific attributes and categories suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also discusses the evaluation of state-of-the-art methods, which is a common practice in information retrieval (cs.IR).
